From Michael Covington Subject Re When are two people married in God's eyes In article A Robert Anderson writes I would like to get your opinions on this when exactly does an engaged couple become married in God's eyes Not if they are unwilling to go through a public marriage ceremony nor if they say they are willing but have not actually done Let's distinguish real logistical problems like being stranded on a desert island from excuses such as waiting for so and so's brother to come back from being in the army so he can be in the ceremony Michael Covington Associate Research Scientist Artificial Intelligence Programs The University of Georgia phone Athens Georgia amateur radio